{"id":6400115259,"url":"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7156/6400115259_e988f36790.jpg","path":"7db/627/7db627e18ba711915a1d4be39bc5d31.jpg","date":"2011-11-09","year":2011,"month":11,"lon":-4.416503,"lat":60.710823,"tags":"aqua,clouds,modis,nasa","S2CellId":"5377000000000000","result":6058,"accuracy":0.0111246025,"title":"Ship+Wave+Clouds+over+the+North+Sea","description":"To+download+the+full+resolution+and+other+files+go+to%3A+%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fearthobservatory.nasa.gov%2FIOTD%2Fview.php%3Fid%3D76524%26src%3Dflickr%22+rel%3D%22nofollow%22%3Eearthobservatory.nasa.gov%2FIOTD%2Fview.php%3Fid%3D76524%26src%3D...%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%0AIf+air+were+visible%2C+it+would+be+a+thing+of+mesmerizing+beauty+and+motion.+Air+courses+in+streams+and+eddies%3B+it+rises+and+falls+and+flows.+This+image%2C+taken+by+the+Moderate+Resolution+Imaging+Spectroradiometer+%28MODIS%29+on+NASA%E2%80%99s+Aqua+satellite+on+November+9%2C+2011%2C+offers+a+rare+snapshot+of+motion+in+the+atmosphere.+Currents+of+air+shaped+an+otherwise+uniform+layer+of+marine+clouds+over+the+North+Sea.%0A%0AAir+moving+over+the+ocean+flows+smoothly+over+the+water+because+it+encounters+no+obstacles.+When+the+air+meets+an+island%2C+it+has+to+lift+up+over+the+land.+What+goes+up+must+come+down%2C+and+the+air+sinks+again.+The+motion+sets+up+a+wave+pattern+that+continues+for+some+time+until+the+energy+is+dissipated.+Like+the+ripples+when+you+toss+a+stone+in+calm+water%2C+the+waves+are+most+distinct+near+the+source+%28the+island%29+and+gradually+become+less+distinct+at+a+distance.%0A%0AThe+rippling+air+shapes+the+low+clouds+in+this+image.+The+clouds+at+the+top+of+the+wave+are+brighter+than+clouds+in+the+trough.+Such+clouds+are+often+called+ship-wave+clouds+because+they+resemble+the+waves+created+by+a+ship+cutting+through+calm+water.%0A%0AIn+the+North+Sea%2C+air+encounters+a+number+of+obstacles+that+create+wave+patterns.+In+some+cases%2C+as+over+the+Faroe+Islands%2C+the+wave+patterns+compliment+one+another%2C+resulting+in+a+wide+swath.+But+in+other+cases%2C+the+waves+created+by+one+island+or+islet+interact+with+waves+created+by+another.+The+result+is+a+mishmash+of+circular+waves+in+a+classic+interference+pattern.%0A%0AObserving+similar+interference+patterns+in+water+helped+scientists+understand+the+wave+nature+of+light.+In+the+early+1800s%2C+Thomas+Young+identified+interference+patterns+when+two+beams+of+light+interact.%0A%0ANASA+image+courtesy+Jeff+Schmaltz%2C+LANCE%2FEOSDIS+MODIS+Rapid+Response+Team+at+NASA+GSFC.+Caption+by+Holli+Riebeek.+%0A%0AThe+%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fearthobservatory.nasa.gov%2F%3Fsrc%3Dflickr%22+rel%3D%22nofollow%22%3EEarth+Observatory%27s%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E+mission+is+to+share+with+the+public+the+images%2C+stories%2C+and+discoveries+about+climate+and+the+environment+that+emerge+from+NASA+research%2C+including+its+satellite+missions%2C+in-the-field+research%2C+and+climate+models.%0A%0A%3Cstrong%3ELike+us+on+%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FNASAEarthObservatory%22+rel%3D%22nofollow%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%0A%0A%3Cstrong%3EFollow+us+on+%3Ca+href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnasa_eo%22+rel%3D%22nofollow%22%3ETwitter%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%0A%0A%3Cstrong%3EAdd+us+to+your+circles+on+%3Ca+href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fplus.google.com%2Fu%2F0%2Fb%2F107502325821816920399%2F%22+rel%3D%22nofollow%22%3EGoogle%2B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E"}
